condition.narrative: Article 5.01. The Additional Conditions of Effectiveness consist of the following, namely, that the Borrower, through the JMT, hasupdated the Project Operations Manual for the purposes of this Loan, in a manner satisfactory to the Bank.

Finance Agreement: Chief information and technology officer: Section I.A.2. of Schedule 2 | Description: The Borrower, through theMOJ, shall retain a chief information and technology officer within the JMT with responsibilities acceptable to the Bank. |Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement: Environmental Safeguards: Section C.1. of Schedule 2 | Description: The Borrower shall ensure that the Projectis carried out in accordance with the EMP and RPF, and shall ensure that all measures necessary for the carrying out of the EMP andRPF shall be taken in a timely manner. Except as the Bank shall otherwise agree, the Borrower shall not assign, amend, abrogate orwaive the EMP and/or RPF. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement: Environmental Safeguards: Section C.2. of Schedule 2 | Description: Prior to the commencement of works for eachproposed site, the Borrower shall ensure that: (a) the related site-specific EMPs are prepared in accordance with the EMP; (b) theproposed design and site for said works incorporate the provisions of site-specific EMPs; (c) the provisions of said site-specificEMPs are adequately included in the proposed contract for said works; and (d) such works are carried out in accordance with therespective site-specific EMPs. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement: Information technology department in MOJ - establishment: Section I.A.3. of Schedule 2 | Description: TheBorrower, through the MOJ, shall establish by no later than January 1, 2016 an information technology department in the MOJ, withresources and responsibilities acceptable to the Bank, and with competent staff in adequate numbers. | Due Date :01-Jan-2016

Finance Agreement: Information technology department in MOJ - maintenance: Section I.A.3. of Schedule 2 | Description: TheBorrower, through the MOJ, shall maintain an information technology department in the MOJ, with resources and responsibilitiesacceptable to the Bank, and with competent staff in adequate numbers. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement: Institutional arrangements: Section I.A.1. of Schedule 2 | Description: The Borrower shall vest the overallresponsibility for the implementation of the Project in the JMT and shall maintain the JMT, at all times during Projectimplementation, with resources and responsibilities acceptable to the Bank, and with competent staff in adequate numbers. TheBorrower shall ensure that the JMT shall carry out the Project in accordance with the Operational Manual and, except as the Bankshall otherwise agree, shall not amend, suspend, abrogate, repeal or waive any provision of said Manual without the prior writtenapproval of the Bank. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement: Social Safeguards: Section C.3. of Schedule 2 | Description: The Borrower shall ensure that the RAPs: (a) shallbe prepared in a manner satisfactory to the Bank in accordance with the RPF prior to commencement of any activities for the areaswhere physical relocation, land acquisition and/or loss of income due to the Project activities have been identified, and; (b)shall be carried out in a timely manner, satisfactory to the Bank. In the event that land acquisition or resettlement is requiredfor the purposes of carrying out activities, the Borrower shall (a) notify the Bank of any intended acquisition of land orresettlement; (b) disclose the RPF and each RAP (if any) prepared under the Project, and; (c) ensure that the MOJ causes all landacquisition and resettlement under the Project to be undertaken in accordance with the provisions and procedures contained in theRPF and the respective RAP, and that all relevant information is adequately provided to all affected persons, and potentiallyaffected persons, in a timely and adequate manner. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

title.narrative: Improved Access: Increased access to services by different groups of users in all six court jurisdictions

Users expressing satisfaction with access, transparency and efficiency of selected justice services
Justice Sector Gender Strategy and Action Plan is publicly available
MOJ IT Call Center and Help Desk operational
Disputes processed using mediation mechanisms in select court jurisdictions in Baku, Sheki and Sumgayit
Piloting of TT prototypes for productivity and efficiency gains
Number of people trained for the use of e-applications
Courts and other justice sector entitites connected to e-Courts
Improved Efficiency: Increased efficiency of service delivery
Average energy consumption in JSSIP-financed 'smart courts' - kilowatt-hours per square meter per annum
Global Data Management Community (DAMA International) metrics applied to at least one database
Guidelines for using transformative technologies developed, including assessment of readiness and risk mitigation capabilities
Information on construction activities is publicly accessible
Audio-video court proceedings transcription system operational in all six court jurisdictions
Number of uncontested civil enforcement cases electronically processed
